message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Tonga in the past 20 years was the coronation of King Tupou VI in 2015. This event marked the transition of power from his late brother, King George Tupou V, who passed away in 2012. The coronation ceremony was a grand and elaborate affair, attended by dignitaries from around the world. It symbolized the continuation of Tonga's monarchy and the country's commitment to its traditional cultural values.
